-- Galliford Try’s Fitzgerald Says U.K. Mortgage Market ‘Easing’
-- B y   C o l m   H e a t l e y
-- 2012-02-22T08:10:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-22/galliford-try-s-fitzgerald-says-u-k-mortgage-market-easing-.html
The availability of U.K. mortgages
is getting better and house prices have “reached the bottom,”
Greg Fitzgerald, Chief Executive Officer of Galliford Try said
today in a phone interview.  “The mortgage market is definitely easing,” Fitzgerald
said. “Sales are better during 2012. We’ve had a great start to
2012.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
